# ADR-001: Initial Architecture

**Date:** $(date +%Y-%m-%d)
**Status:** Accepted

## Context

This service was scaffolded using Forge CLI to follow organizational standards.

## Decision

| Aspect | Choice |
|--------|--------|
| Runtime | Java 21 (LTS) |
| Framework | Spring Boot 4.0.5 |
| Database | SQL Server (Azure SQL) |
| Auth | <%= authPattern %> |
| Messaging | <%= messaging %> |
| Observability | OpenTelemetry, Logstash JSON, Prometheus |
| Resilience | Resilience4j (circuit breaker, retry, bulkhead, time limiter) |
| Testing | JUnit 5, TestContainers (SQL Server), MockMvc |
| Build | Maven, JaCoCo (85% coverage minimum) |
| Container | Multi-stage Dockerfile, layered jar, non-root user |

## Consequences

- All developers need Docker for local development (SQL Server + TestContainers)
<%_ if (messaging === 'Kafka') { -%>
- Kafka must be available locally (Docker Compose recommended)
<%_ } -%>
- Security is always on (even with auth=None, security headers are applied)
- Coverage enforcement may require writing tests before new features pass CI
